[2] Indonesia (Nationwide)
Date: 20 Feb 2007
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@thomson.com>
Source: ReliefWeb Geneva, Switzerland [edited]
<http://www.reliefweb.int/rw/RWB.NSF/db900SID/LSGZ-6YLHF3?OpenDocument>

The total number of deaths from seasonal dengue fever in Indonesia
since January this year [2007] has reached 330 out of 23 000 infected
people, the Health Ministry said here on Tuesday [20 Feb 2007].
Head of the Sub Directorate of Arbovirosis in the ministry Rita
Kriastuti said that the death figure from the disease has risen
sharply and that it could be curtailed through an implementation of
good hygiene and sanitation measures. "The number of cases could be
decreased by a good implementation of sanitation and hygiene," said Kriastuti.
The disease has attacked many provinces in the vast archipelago
country, such as Jakarta, West Java, Central Java, East Java and East
Kalimantan, the ministry said.
The health ministry has taken several measures to decrease the rate
of fatalities from the mosquito-borne disease, which spreads during
the rainy season, according the ministry.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
